data.title: Melaleuca viminalis (Sol. ex Gaertn.) Byrnes
data.meta_description: The native range of this species is Queensland to New South Wales. It is a shrub and grows primarily in the subtropical biome. It is used as invertebrate food, has environmental uses and for fuel.
